---
// No utils nor props for this component
import "@styles/faq.css";
---


<!-- ============================================ -->
<!--                    FAQ                       -->
<!-- ============================================ -->

<section id="faq">
  <div class="cs-container">
    <div class="cs-content">
      <span class="cs-topper">Company Name Ltd.</span>
      <h2 class="cs-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <p class="cs-text">Have some questions? Check out our FAQ, where we answer our most common questions.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cs-flex-group">
      <ul class="cs-faq-group">
        <li class="cs-faq-item active">
          <button class="cs-button">How long does a construction project usually take?</button>
          <p class="cs-item-p">Project timelines depend on the size and complexity of the build. 
            Smaller renovation projects can take a few weeks, while full home builds or major structural work may take several months. 
            Once we review your plans, we provide a clear timeline and keep you updated throughout the process.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="cs-faq-item">
          <button class="cs-button">What’s the difference between a fixed price and a staged payment plan?</button>
          <p class="cs-item-p">
            The main difference is how payments are structured.
            With a fixed price, you receive a detailed quote upfront and the total project cost is agreed before work begins.
            With a staged payment plan, payments are divided into milestones (e.g., foundation, structure, roofing, finishing).
            This makes budgeting more manageable and ensures transparency at every stage. The best option depends on your budget, project scope, and financial planning preferences.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="cs-faq-item">
          <button class="cs-button">Do you charge VAT?</button>
          <p class="cs-item-p">We work with a trusted network of licensed subcontractors for specialized tasks such as electrical, plumbing, and roofing. 
            All professionals we work with meet industry standards and are fully qualified.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="cs-faq-item">
          <button class="cs-button">What are the advantages of hiring a professional construction company?</button>
          <p class="cs-item-p">
            Working with an experienced construction team ensures: Compliance with local building regulations, 
            High-quality workmanship, Proper project management, Cost control and budgeting accuracy, Long-term structural safety
            We focus on doing things properly the first time, prioritizing quality and long-term durability over shortcuts.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="cs-faq-item">
          <button class="cs-button">Is my construction project insured and protected?</button>
          <p class="cs-item-p">Yes. We carry appropriate insurance coverage, and all work is completed according to current safety regulations and building codes. 
            This protects both your property and our team throughout the project.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="cs-faq-item">
          <button class="cs-button">Do you help with permits and approvals?</button>
          <p class="cs-item-p">Yes. We can assist with planning permissions, building permits, and necessary inspections depending on your location and project type.
             We ensure your project meets all legal and regulatory requirements.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li class="cs-faq-item">
          <button class="cs-button">How soon can you start my project?</button>
          <p class="cs-item-p">
            Start times depend on current workload and project scope. 
            After our initial consultation and approval of the quote, we’ll provide a clear start date and estimated completion timeline.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="cs-faq-item">
          <button class="cs-button">Is the construction compliant with regulations and standards?</button>
          <p class="cs-item-p">Yes. All projects are completed in accordance with local building codes, safety standards, and environmental regulations. 
            Quality control and compliance are central to everything we do.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="cs-cta">
        <h3 class="cs-h3">Don’t see the answer you need?</h3>
        <p class="cs-cta-p">That’s ok. Just drop a message and we will get back to you ASAP.</p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid">Contact Us!</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
	// Paste the JS inside Astro:page-load wrapper for View Transitions purposes
	document.addEventListener("astro:page-load", () => {
		const faqItems = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(".cs-faq-item"));
		for (const item of faqItems) {
			const onClick = () => {
				item.classList.toggle("active");
			};
			item.addEventListener("click", onClick);
		}
	});
</script>
